        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>black olives</strong> in half</p><p>Chop the <strong>remaining garlic </strong>finely</p><p>Grind the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped olives </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) with a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> to form a paste</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and mix well – this is your <strong>olive tapenade</strong></p><p>Tip: Don't have a pestle & mortar? Pulse in a food processor!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
